      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  Success! Homage to the Lord,
	  the perfectly Enlightened One,
	  of the Great Caitya at Adhāloka.
	  In the year 35 of King
	  <persName key="pers:VpŚrīPuḷumāvi">Vāsiṣṭhīputra
	    Śrī Puḷumāvi</persName>,
	  in the second half-month of summer, on the 
	  tenth day. An agaraka and a covering with slabs
	  are the pious gift of the nun from the Koru family,
	  <persName key="pers:Kan-Dharmaśrī">Dharmaśrī</persName>,
	  together with (my) parents and with my teacher,
	  the venerable <persName key="pers:Kan-BhVaraṇabhūti">Varaṇabhūti</persName>,
	  and with the Venerable 
	  <persName key="pers:Kan-BhSiṃha">Siṃha</persName>, and
	  for the well-being and happiness of all beings.
	</p>
